# CWE-321 remediation: private keys must never be committed.
# 1. Remove the key from the repo and purge it from git history.
# 2. Revoke/rotate the key pair immediately (assume it is compromised).
# 3. Store the new private key in a secret manager / HSM; reference it at runtime.
# 4. Add `*.key` and `id_*`/`*_rsa` patterns to .gitignore.
# (No key material is stored in this file.)
